# Version Management

## Single Source of Truth

The app version is defined in `src/Clipt/Clipt.csproj` via the `<Version>` property. This is the ONLY place the version number lives in source code.

The Inno Setup installer at `installer/Clipt.iss` has its own `#define MyAppVersion` that MUST be kept in sync manually.

## Rules

1. **Every feature, fix, or meaningful change MUST include a version bump** in both:
   - `src/Clipt/Clipt.csproj` — the `<Version>` property
   - `installer/Clipt.iss` — the `#define MyAppVersion` line

2. **Versioning scheme**: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH` (SemVer)
   - MAJOR: breaking changes
   - MINOR: new features
   - PATCH: bug fixes, tweaks

3. **Title bars MUST show the version**. The `MainWindow` title is set in code-behind from the assembly version. If adding new windows, include the version in their title too.

4. **Read version at runtime** via:
   ```csharp
   var version = System.Reflection.Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().GetName().Version;
   var versionStr = $"{version.Major}.{version.Minor}.{version.Build}";
   ```
